description:
Last but not least, introducing Lauren!

Name: Lauren
Pronouns: she/her
Year and program: U2 Anthropology + Religious Studies
Hometown: Surrey, BC. 
Religious studies class you wish existed: Something on contemporary religion/new religious movements would be cool! Or…something about the connection between visual art/images and religion! 
Advice for religious studies students: Do your readings!! It might seem obvious but you truly get out what you put in! 
Favourite thing to cook: Dumplings 🥟

Introducing myself :)

Name: Aria Lucyk
Pronouns: she/her
Year and program: U3 Double major in Religious Studies and Psychology
Hometown: REGINA, SASKATCHEWAN!!!
Religious studies class you wish existed: Religion and International Law, or the Psychology of Religious Texts and Myths
Advice for religious studies students: Get to know your professors, never be afraid to ask “stupid” questions
Favourite thing to cook: Risotto

Introducing Sophie! 

Name: Sophie Rose
Pronouns: She/her
Year and program: Joint Honours Religious Studies and Political Science
Hometown: Toronto 
Religious studies class you wish existed: Religion, Irreligion, and Media
Advice for religious studies students: Utilize the birks chapel
Favourite thing to cook: Various forms of potato
